These days I was fiddling around with one particular parameterization for Lambert curve. Although it was not that hard, I was happy that finally I made it clear.
The problem is like this: a Lambert curve is a curve given by [C = {(z,w) \; | \; z = w e^w } \subset \mathbb{C}^* \times \mathbb{C}^*.] Note that the above equation defines (w) as an implicit function of (z).</description>
